                          "String": "AEROBIC: In an artificial stream, microbial degradation became significant after 3 weeks and accounted for 26-46% removal(1). Pentachlorophenol mineralization in the relatively unpolluted water of Long Island Sound and water from several sites in the Hudson Estuary in summer was also very low (<5 ng/L per day)(2). 3 and 5 ppm pentachlorophenol were completely degraded in 38 and 57 days, respectively, when incubated in Pennsylvania and Virginia unsaturated soils taken at 4 and 4.5 m depths(3). Median lag times of 71, 56, and 41 days and median half-lives of 39, 13, and 9 days were observed in a degradation study on three surface water samples using a shake-flask die-away procedure(4). Results suggest that biodegradation potential increases with added sediment(4).",
